addEventListener.description:
Appends an event listener for events whose type attribute value is type. The callback argument sets the callback that will be invoked when the event is dispatched.

The options argument sets listener-specific options. For compatibility this can be a boolean, in which case the method behaves exactly as if the value was specified as options's capture.

When set to true, options's capture prevents callback from being invoked when the event's eventPhase attribute value is BUBBLING_PHASE. When false (or not present), callback will not be invoked when event's eventPhase attribute value is CAPTURING_PHASE. Either way, callback will be invoked if event's eventPhase attribute value is AT_TARGET.

When set to true, options's passive indicates that the callback will not cancel the event by invoking preventDefault(). This is used to enable performance optimizations described in ยง 2.8 Observing event listeners.

When set to true, options's once indicates that the callback will only be invoked once after which the event listener will be removed.

If an AbortSignal is passed for options's signal, then the event listener will be removed when signal is aborted.

The event listener is appended to target's event listener list and is not appended if it has the same type, callback, and capture.

closest.description: Returns the first (starting at element) inclusive ancestor that matches selectors, and null otherwise.

compareDocumentPosition.description: Returns a bitmask indicating the position of other relative to node.

contains.description: Returns true if other is an inclusive descendant of node, and false otherwise.

dispatchEvent.description: Dispatches a synthetic event event to target and returns true if either event's cancelable attribute value is false or its preventDefault() method was not invoked, and false otherwise.

DOCUMENT_POSITION_CONTAINED_BY.description: Set when other is a descendant of node.

DOCUMENT_POSITION_CONTAINS.description: Set when other is an ancestor of node.

DOCUMENT_POSITION_DISCONNECTED.description: Set when node and other are not in the same tree.

DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING.description: Set when other is following node.

DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING.description: Set when other is preceding node.

element.description: Overrides the default element name to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider

firstElementChild.description: Returns the first child that is an element, and null otherwise.

getAttribute.description: Returns element's first attribute whose qualified name is qualifiedName, and null if there is no such attribute otherwise.

getAttributeNames.description: Returns the qualified names of all element's attributes. Can contain duplicates.

getAttributeNS.description: Returns element's attribute whose namespace is namespace and local name is localName, and null if there is no such attribute otherwise.

getElementsByClassName.description: Returns a HTMLCollection of the elements in the object on which the method was invoked (a document or an element) that have all the classes given by classNames. The classNames argument is interpreted as a space-separated list of classes.

hasAttribute.description: Returns true if element has an attribute whose qualified name is qualifiedName, and false otherwise.

hasAttributeNS.description: Returns true if element has an attribute whose namespace is namespace and local name is localName.

hasAttributes.description: Returns true if element has attributes, and false otherwise.

id.description: Returns the value of element's id content attribute. Can be set to change it.

isConnected.description: Returns true if node is connected and false otherwise.

isEqualNode.description: Returns whether node and otherNode have the same properties.

lastElementChild.description: Returns the last child that is an element, and null otherwise.

matches.description: Returns true if matching selectors against element's root yields element, and false otherwise.

nextElementSibling.description: Returns the first following sibling that is an element, and null otherwise.

nodeName.description: Returns a string appropriate for the type of node.

normalize.description: Removes empty exclusive Text nodes and concatenates the data of remaining contiguous exclusive Text nodes into the first of their nodes.

onabort.description: Fires when the user aborts the download.

onblur.description: Fires when the object loses the input focus.

oncanplay.description: Occurs when playback is possible, but would require further buffering.

onchange.description: Fires when the contents of the object or selection have changed.

onclick.description: Fires when the user clicks the left mouse button on the object

oncontextmenu.description: Fires when the user clicks the right mouse button in the client area, opening the context menu.

ondblclick.description: Fires when the user double-clicks the object.

ondrag.description: Fires on the source object continuously during a drag operation.

ondragend.description: Fires on the source object when the user releases the mouse at the close of a drag operation.

ondragenter.description: Fires on the target element when the user drags the object to a valid drop target.

ondragleave.description: Fires on the target object when the user moves the mouse out of a valid drop target during a drag operation.

ondragover.description: Fires on the target element continuously while the user drags the object over a valid drop target.

ondragstart.description: Fires on the source object when the user starts to drag a text selection or selected object.

ondurationchange.description: Occurs when the duration attribute is updated.

onemptied.description: Occurs when the media element is reset to its initial state.

onended.description: Occurs when the end of playback is reached.

onerror.description: Fires when an error occurs during object loading.

onfocus.description: Fires when the object receives focus.

onkeydown.description: Fires when the user presses a key.

onkeypress.description: Fires when the user presses an alphanumeric key.

onkeyup.description: Fires when the user releases a key.

onload.description: Fires immediately after the browser loads the object.

onloadeddata.description: Occurs when media data is loaded at the current playback position.

onloadedmetadata.description: Occurs when the duration and dimensions of the media have been determined.

onloadstart.description: Occurs when Internet Explorer begins looking for media data.

onmousedown.description: Fires when the user clicks the object with either mouse button.

onmousemove.description: Fires when the user moves the mouse over the object.

onmouseout.description: Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer outside the boundaries of the object.

onmouseover.description: Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer into the object.

onmouseup.description: Fires when the user releases a mouse button while the mouse is over the object.

onplay.description: Occurs when the play method is requested.

onplaying.description: Occurs when the audio or video has started playing.

onprogress.description: Occurs to indicate progress while downloading media data.

onratechange.description: Occurs when the playback rate is increased or decreased.

onreset.description: Fires when the user resets a form.

onscroll.description: Fires when the user repositions the scroll box in the scroll bar on the object.

onseeked.description: Occurs when the seek operation ends.

onseeking.description: Occurs when the current playback position is moved.

onselect.description: Fires when the current selection changes.

onstalled.description: Occurs when the download has stopped.

onsuspend.description: Occurs if the load operation has been intentionally halted.

ontimeupdate.description: Occurs to indicate the current playback position.

onvolumechange.description: Occurs when the volume is changed, or playback is muted or unmuted.

onwaiting.description: Occurs when playback stops because the next frame of a video resource is not available.

ownerDocument.description: Returns the node document. Returns null for documents.

prepend.description:
Inserts nodes before the first child of node, while replacing strings in nodes with equivalent Text nodes.

Throws a "HierarchyRequestError" DOMException if the constraints of the node tree are violated.

previousElementSibling.description: Returns the first preceding sibling that is an element, and null otherwise.

querySelectorAll.description: Returns all element descendants of node that match selectors.

removeAttribute.description: Removes element's first attribute whose qualified name is qualifiedName.

removeAttributeNS.description: Removes element's attribute whose namespace is namespace and local name is localName.

replaceChildren.description:
Replace all children of node with nodes, while replacing strings in nodes with equivalent Text nodes.

Throws a "HierarchyRequestError" DOMException if the constraints of the node tree are violated.

replaceWith.description:
Replaces node with nodes, while replacing strings in nodes with equivalent Text nodes.

Throws a "HierarchyRequestError" DOMException if the constraints of the node tree are violated.

requestFullscreen.description:
Displays element fullscreen and resolves promise when done.

When supplied, options's navigationUI member indicates whether showing navigation UI while in fullscreen is preferred or not. If set to "show", navigation simplicity is preferred over screen space, and if set to "hide", more screen space is preferred. User agents are always free to honor user preference over the application's. The default value "auto" indicates no application preference.

setAttribute.description: Sets the value of element's first attribute whose qualified name is qualifiedName to value.

setAttributeNS.description: Sets the value of element's attribute whose namespace is namespace and local name is localName to value.

shadowRoot.description: Returns element's shadow root, if any, and if shadow root's mode is "open", and null otherwise.

slot.description: Returns the value of element's slot content attribute. Can be set to change it.

toggleAttribute.type:
(
  qualifiedName: string,
  force?: boolean | undefined
) => boolean
toggleAttribute.description:
If force is not given, "toggles" qualifiedName, removing it if it is present and adding it if it is not present. If force is true, adds qualifiedName. If force is false, removes qualifiedName.

Returns true if qualifiedName is now present, and false otherwise.
